500|$|Another {{important}} aspect of St Kildan life was the daily [...] "parliament". This was a meeting held in the street every morning after prayers and attended by all the adult males {{during the course of}} which they would decide upon the day's activities. No one led the meeting, and all men had the right to speak. According to Steel (1988), [...] "Discussion frequently spread discord, but never in recorded history were feuds so bitter as to bring about a permanent division in the community". This notion of <b>a</b> <b>free</b> <b>society</b> influenced Enric Miralles' vision for the new Scottish Parliament Building, opened in October 2004.|$|E
